**012_USB_HID_Mouse**

Simple Mouse Emulator based on nano board, MPU6050 accelerometer placed on board is used.
MCU USB is configured in FS-Mode as a HID-Class Device sending Mouse report each 5 ms.
Report is based on data from accelerometer transmitted via I2C and state of GPIO pins used as Mouse Left and Right Buttons.
Changing yaw angle of board makes cursor move horizontally (negative - left, positive - right).
Changing pitch angle of board makes cursor move vertically (negative - down, positive - up).
